# Source Directory Structure

The `src` directory contains the main React/TypeScript application code. Here's the key structure:

## Entry Points
- [main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx) - Application entry point
- [App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Root component with main layout and routing
- [App.css](mdc:src/App.css) and [App.module.css](mdc:src/App.module.css) - Global and component-specific styles

## Core Directories
- `components/` - Reusable React components
- `stores/` - State management stores
- `services/` - API and service integrations
- `types/` - TypeScript type definitions
- `utils/` - Utility functions and helpers
- `config/` - Application configuration
- `assets/` - Static assets like images
- `styles/` - Global styles and theme definitions

## Configuration
- [config.ts](mdc:src/config.ts) - Central configuration file
- [vite-env.d.ts](mdc:src/vite-env.d.ts) - Vite environment type declarations
